[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+     15[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;192;197;206mRecurring Chapter 2 hygiene is largely addressed. IAM permissions row says "Scope every action to specific resource ARNs." The VPC endpoint list is complete (Transcribe, Bedrock, Bedrock Runtime, Comprehend Medical, KMS, Secrets Manager, Step Functions, CloudWatch Logs, CloudWatch Monitoring, HealthLake plus S3 and DynamoDB gateway endpoints), and the per-AZ-per-endpoint cost reminder is folded into the cost estimate. The Bedrock model-invocation-logging PHI-store note is present and correctly scoped ("will contain the transcript and the draft note; log destination must be KMS-encrypted to the same standard as the note archive"). The Guardrails contextual-grounding discussion names the explicit grounding-source tagging requirement and the correct [38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;163;190;140mamazon-bedrock-guardrailAction[38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;192;197;206m intervention-detection field (fixing the issue flagged in Recipe 2.6's expert review). No em dashes (direct U+2014 and U+2013 check: zero matches). Audio is correctly treated as "always PHI (voice is biometric)" and the re-identification-risk distinction between transcript de-identification and audio de-identification is called out. Two-party consent jurisdictions, mid-encounter consent withdrawal, sensitive encounter exclusions, and pediatric consent are all addressed. The architecture diagram includes a validation-exhausted exit path routing to a human-review queue (the diagram flaw that appeared in Recipe 2.6 and Recipe 2.7's A3 is not repeated here).[K
