[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    248[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m The "Honest Take" is the strongest in Chapter 2 alongside Recipe 2.7's. "Ambient documentation is not a transcription service, and it's not a clinical decision support tool. It's a workflow tool that happens to use AI." Six specific patterns that work ("start with a narrow specialty and a narrow encounter type," "treat the consent experience as a product," "pair clinicians with a real-time support channel during rollout," "make the review UX obviously transparent," "measure edit distance religiously," "don't skip the case review program") and six harder truths ("the 'solves burnout' framing oversells," "failure modes are worst for patients who are hardest to serve," "not every specialty benefits equally," "clinicians will edit the draft. Every time," "patients will occasionally ask for a copy of what was recorded"). This section is publication-ready.[K
