The companion walks through the five pseudocode steps from the main recipe:[0m[0m
[0m[0m
1. [1mAssemble features[22m — merges patient-level features from SageMaker Feature Store with appointment-derived features, with a clean cold-start path for new patients[0m[0m
2. [1mScore the appointment[22m — loads a scikit-learn Pipeline from S3 and produces a probability; uses a DataFrame so training/serving feature contracts match[0m[0m
3. [1mCompute baseline deviation and route[22m — batch-reads patient baselines from DynamoDB, computes per-patient deviation, applies HIGH_RISK and DEVIATION thresholds, caps outreach at daily capacity, and writes to the appropriate queue table[0m[0m
4. [1mExecute outreach[22m — selects channels from patient preferences, sends via Pinpoint (SMS/voice/email) with minimum-necessary PHI in message bodies, logs every intervention[0m[0m
5. [1mCapture outcome and close the loop[22m — joins outcome events to prediction archives and intervention logs, derives a training label, updates the rolling baseline with exponential decay, writes labels to S3[0m[0m
[0m[0m
The file also includes a [38;5;10mretrain_monthly[0m sketch showing subgroup AUC evaluation as a fairness gate and a detailed "Gap to Production" section covering idempotency, VPC deployment, KMS, Pinpoint HIPAA config, intervention effect measurement, and override workflows.[0m[0m
