[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    1719[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    1720[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mError handling.[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;192;197;206m The example's error handling is minimal. In production, wrap each external call in try/except with structured logging, emit a failure metric, and route the affected provider to a dead-letter queue for operations review. Do not silently swallow DynamoDB throttling, Athena query failures, or S3 access-denied errors; each is a different class of problem with a different mitigation.[K
